This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for estimating the quality of machine translation systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses Naive Bayes classifier, which is a popular machine learning algorithm, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves feature extraction and classification, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively.
